Calpers Plans to Vote Against BP Accounts at AGM, Times Reports

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-04-12T22:04:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/calpers-plans-to-vote-against-bp-accounts-at-agm-times-reports.html
The  California Public Employees’
Retirement System  will vote at  BP Plc (BP/) ’s annual general meeting
in  London  tomorrow to reject the company’s accounts because it
says it cannot support BP following the Gulf of Mexico spill
last year, the London-based Times reported. Calpers will also
vote against the reappointment of William Castell, chairman of
the oil company’s safety, ethics and environment committee, as a
non-executive director, the newspaper said.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
